column20: Possessing a calm demeanor, this Pokémon was revered as a deity incarnate before it was identified as a regional variant of Ninetales.

column19: As a result of Mega Evolution, its power has been entirely converted into psychic energy, and it has lost all strength in its muscles.
column20: Its hidden psychic power has been unleashed. A glance at someone gives it knowledge of the course of that person’s life, from birth to death.

column19: All the energy from Mega Evolution poured into the Shellder on its tail, leaving Slowpoke to be swallowed whole.
column20: When bathed in the energy of Mega Evolution, Shellder converts into impregnable armor. There is virtually no change in Slowpoke.

column19: The garbage it eats causes continuous chemical changes in its body, which produce its exceedingly vivid coloration.
column20: While it’s unexpectedly quiet and friendly, if it’s not fed any trash for a while, it will smash its Trainer’s furnishings and eat up the fragments.

column19: Gengar’s relationships are warped. It has no interest in opponents unless it perceives them as prey.
column20: The energy of Mega Evolution awakened it. It sinks into another dimension, where it keeps a patient watch for its chance to attack.

column19: Alola is the best environment for this Pokémon. Local people take pride in its appearance, saying this is how Exeggutor ought to look.
column20: As it grew taller and taller, it outgrew its reliance on psychic powers, while within it awakened the power of the sleeping dragon.

column19: The bones it possesses were once its mother’s. Its mother’s regrets have become like a vengeful spirit protecting this Pokémon.
column20: Its custom is to mourn its lost companions. Mounds of dirt by the side of the road mark the graves of the Marowak.

column19: Mega Kangaskhan’s strength derives from the mother’s happiness about her child’s growth. Watching it grow up keeps her spirits high.
column20: Thanks to Mega Evolution, its child grows. But as the child is good only at fighting and nothing else, its mother feels uneasy about its future.

column19: The influence of Mega Evolution leaves it in a state of constant excitement. It pierces enemies with its two large horns before shredding them.
column20: Bathed in the energy of Mega Evolution, its wings become unusually developed. It flies at speeds of approximately 30 mph.

column19: Mega Evolution also affects its brain, leaving no other function except its destructive instinct to burn everything to cinders.
column20: It jets water from the orifices on its sides, streaking above the water surface at supersonic speed.

column19: Part of its body has become stone. Some scholars claim that this is Aerodactyl’s true appearance.
column20: When it Mega Evolves, it becomes more vicious than ever before. Some say that’s because its excess of power is causing it pain.

column19: The excess energy that bathes this Pokémon keeps it in constant danger of overflow. It can’t sustain a battle over long periods of time.
column20: Due to the effects of Mega Evolution, its pincers have taken on a more diabolical form, ripping anything they pinch to shreds.

column19: The jewel from its chest, which has grown gigantic due to the effects of Mega Evolution, can turn back any attack.
column20: Supporting a giant heavy jewel, it can’t change direction very nimbly and is vulnerable to attack from behind.

column19: The spines sprouting from its head are transformed fangs. If they’re injured or broken off, the spines will regenerate countless times.
column20: As a consequence of Mega Evolution, its combative instincts exploded. The yellow marks it bears are scars from a long history of battles.

column19: When this Pokémon whips the winglike fur on its back as though beating its wings, it sends an intimidating aura flying at its opponents.
column20: As the energy of Mega Evolution fills it, its fur bristles. What you see on its back are not true wings, and this Pokémon isn’t able to fly.

column19: Anyone standing in its path gets sliced right in two, while this Pokémon continues its flight without interruption.
column20: Mega Evolution fuels its brutality, and it may even turn on the Trainer who raised it. It’s been dubbed “the blood-soaked crescent.”

column19: This form results from one Metagross, one Metang, and two Beldum linking up.
column20: Mega Evolution stimulated its brain. It emerged as a ruthless Pokémon that will clutch at any means of ensuring its victories.

column19: Excess energy melted its arms and wings, transforming them into giant scythes.
column20: Its vaunted wings become scythes, sending it mad with rage. It swings its scythes wildly and slices the ground to pieces.

column19: Black streaks all over its body show where its auras and the energy of Mega Evolution intermingled and raced through it.
column20: It readies itself to face its enemies by focusing its mental energies. Its fighting style can be summed up in a single word: heartless.

column19: Its sharp fangs make short work of finishing off its enemies, but it’s unable to maintain this body indefinitely. After a period of time, it falls apart.
column20: This is Zygarde’s form when about 10% of its cells have been gathered. It runs across the land at speeds greater than 60 mph.
